data.title: Only Tacos?
data.text:
I have often driven by Jonesy's Tacos and wondered how a stand alone taco restaurant could survive and thrive away from other establishments.  The answer is with a full Mexican menu in addition to burgers and such.

Jonesy's Tacos has seating for 77 in a restaurant set-up.  I think they do a heavy carry out business.  We each had the number one item on the menu as it was our waitress recommendation.  My husband had an enchilada and I had a soft taco, Both of these came with rice and refried beans.  The meal was American Mexican with different spice levels of taco sauce.  Our bill with an ice tea for me was $17.00.

This restaurant has been serving this neighborhood for many years.  It is good food and you will enjoy it.
;

data.title: Yummy, need to visit more often !!!
data.text: My family do not live nearby but when in the area we enjoy a good meal for the price. Only one free refill. I normally order water to drink. A decent kids menu. Voices can be a bit loud. $2 Taco Tuesday's. Definitely worth the trip. The value on the tacos are the best. The enchilada are delicious, it's the sauce is creamy goodness .

data.title: Dinner
data.text:
If you love a loaded taco w fresh ground beef cheese lettuce and 
tomatoes all wrapped in a fried flour shell, this is a great stop. Small and off the beaten path but the food is awesome. Enchiladas very good too. Full service and limited liquor or easy takeout. Love this place.

data.title: BEST VALUE IN TOWN
data.text: Best enchilada I have ever had.  Compare this place to anywhere in town and the staff is on it.  Kind, fast, and want to please you and bring you back.  If you are in a Cubs shirt... you better know your cubs history.

data.title: Best food I have eaten in a while
data.text: We stayed at carter lake, and ate here. Needless to say it was and experience of delicious proportions. If we ever go there again... we will likely go eat there again if it is not completely out of our way.

data.title: MM   MMMMMMMMM
data.text: Great tacos as well as other Mexican treats. Real Mexican with large portions with great prices. Have a look you won't be disappointed.

data.title: great mexican food
data.text:
this taco house has fantastic food, great portions and always friendly. 
the prices are more than reasonable and would recommend to anyone who is in the area looking for a great place to eat!

data.title: Home made flour tortias
data.text: I have to admit I am not a big fan of mexican food. I have to be honest i was surprised with how good the nacho supreme was. Sadly, the only thing it had was cheese, meat, and tomatos. I would of like to see it had olives, lettuce, sour cream and other nacho stuff you would see in a taco bell or other mexican eateries. They do have other stuff besides mexican like: hamburger, shrimp, and chicken for the people who don't care as much for the mexican food. they do have a limited beer selection as well. The people there are very friendly which is a plus. I would recommend it to other people

data.title: Good service - Food just okay
data.text: Went here for a late lunch one afternoon. I had been here before many years ago and remembered liking the tacos.  Took my husband who had never been here before and thought the food was just average. I had a taco and he had a beef and chicken enchilada.  We left wishing we had went to one of our other favorite Mexican food spots. Wasn't bad but probably wouldn't go again.   On a positive note, our server was friendly, fast and helpful!!

data.title: Really good food
data.text: This place has the best enchiladas ever.  I have never been a fan of traditional red sauce (any kind of marinara) and they use a brown thicker sauce on the enchilada with melted cheese.  It will knock your socks off!  And the guacamole is awesome and if once in a while they do not have it, it is for a totally great reason.  I go here at least twice a month and when these people cannot find excellent avacados, they do not have the guacamole.  Wonderful standards and great service.

data.title: Good "dive taco" joint
data.text:
It's not fancy, but the food is outstanding. The tacos were great & house salsa is even better. The portions are huge! One taco is plenty.
Half-priced margaritas all day Friday!
